==================================
AWS GLOBAL INFRASTRUCTURE
==================================

1. AWS Regions --------

----------------------------------
An AWS Region is a geographical area
where AWS has data centers.

Each region contains multiple
Availability Zones.

Examples:
- us-east-1  (North Virginia)
- us-west-2  (Oregon)
- ap-south-1 (Mumbai)

Purpose:
Regions help keep data close to users
and improve performance.


2. Availability Zones (AZ)
----------------------------------
Availability Zones are isolated
data centers inside a region.

Each region has multiple AZs.

Example:
ap-south-1a
ap-south-1b
ap-south-1c

Purpose:
If one AZ fails, another AZ continues
running the application.


3. Edge Locations
----------------------------------
Edge Locations are smaller data centers
used for fast content delivery.

They store cached copies of data
closer to users.

Example service:
Amazon CloudFront

Purpose:
- Faster website loading
- Reduced latency


4. AWS Global Infrastructure Benefits
----------------------------------
- High availability
- Fault tolerance
- Low latency
- Global scalability
